  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hawiga Response Plan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In line with the Humanitarian Response Plan 2017 and the Hawiga Response Plan 2017, Danish Demining Group (DDG) proposes to implement its intervention in The Republic of Iraq focusing on the district of Hawiga. 
DDG further proposes to deploy multi - trained Mine Risk Education (MRE), Non-Technical Survey (NTS) and Battle Area Clearance (BAC) teams in Hawiga in order to support the Iraqi Directorate of Mine Action&#xB4;s (DMA) efforts to mitigate the threat of ERW in the area. Emergency MA support is complemented by risk education to further protection and increase physical safety and in line with that DDG intends to target internal displaced persons (IDP&#xB4;s), conflict-affected communities and potential returnees in order to reduce the threat posed by mines/ERW/IEDs, support safe return and assist socio-economic development. DDG will also support Iraqi national authorities to ensure a competent mine action structure and promote adherence to international standards.</narrative>
  </description>
